            <h1>WHY EASTSIDE GALLERY STILL MATTERS</h1>
            <p>The East Side Gallery isn't just a wall. It's the longest open-air gallery in the world, a living memory of division, and one of Berlin's loudest testaments to freedom and creativity. Stretching 1.3 kilometers along the Spree, it's painted with more than 100 murals from artists across the globe. And while it's one of the city's most photographed landmarks, its power goes far beyond Instagram. Here's why this stretch of concrete still matters for every creative visiting Berlin.</p>
        
<section class="grid_1-1">
    <div><h2>A CANVAS OF FREEDOM</h2>
    <p>When the Berlin Wall fell in 1989, the East Side Gallery became more than just a leftover piece of history, it transformed into a canvas of hope. Artists rushed to paint their visions of freedom, unity, and resilience directly onto the wall. Each mural still carries that energy today. Walking along the g allery isn't just about looking at paintings, it's about feeling a city's heartbeat at the very moment it started beating again.</p></div>
